                <note rend="inline" type="source">662.11173 Barley/48: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Poole</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-11-03T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 3, 1928—noon</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 3—9:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>229. Reference my 215 dated October 23, 10 a.m. Have been confidentially informed
                    by a competent officer of the German Foreign Office that the danger of an
                    embargo seems past.</p>
                <p>Have repeated foregoing to London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Poole</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
